<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-632-707  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 632 707.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Industrial Engineering  Nov 1990 v22 n11 p22(4).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>A rules-based system performs features and options system in acomplex C-T-O environment. (configure-to-order) (Make-To-Order)(column)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Dinitz, Michael.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>A configure-to-order environment needs a computer system thatworks specifically within this environment.andP;  There are two mainsystems used for this type of work: rules-based systems, andfeatures and options systems.andP;  The strengths and weaknessesinherent in each of these systems affects the three main parts toa configure-to-order manufacturing environment: time compression,pricing and configuration.andP;  Two software options are available tosuch a system.andP;  The features and options system uses bills ofmaterials to configure a product, while the rules-based systemoperates with implemented rules to govern selections.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     System DesignComputer-aided manufacturingComputer SystemsRule-Based SystemsComparisonCustomizationPriceTime Management.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>